cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the vulnerability of graph convolutional networks (GCNs) in the semi-supervised setting. It may also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it proposes an attack algorithm to compromise the classification accuracy of GCNs. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it mentions social networks as an application scenario. The paper also involves the use of a discriminator, which is a common technique in the field of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper proposes a Greedy-GAN attack, which is a type of generative adversarial network (GAN), falling under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
